Description: Body sherd of East Greek, possibly North Ionian, pottery cup; interior: reserved save for black band with added red band; exterior: reserved; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Probably from the same vessel as GR 1886.4-1.547 (but not joining).
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 350)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 672, no. 311)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.329)
